definitions.definition: ( also figuratively ) An act of fetching , of bringing something from a distance .

subdefinitions.definition: ( computing , specifically ) An act of fetching data .

definitions.definition: The object of fetching ; the source of an attraction ; a force , propensity , or quality which attracts .
An area over which wind is blowing (over water ) and generating waves.
The length of such an area; the distance a wave can travel across a body of water (without obstruction).
A stratagem or trick ; an artifice .
( uncountable ) A game played with a dog in which a person throws an object for the dog to retrieve.

definitions.definition: The apparition of a living person ; a person's double , the sight of which is supposedly a sign that they are fated to die soon, a doppelganger ; a wraith ( “ a person's likeness seen just after their death ; a ghost , a spectre ” ) .

main_definition: ( originally Ireland , dialectal ) The apparition of a living person ; a person's double , the sight of which is supposedly a sign that they are fated to die soon, a doppelganger ; a wraith ( “ a person's likeness seen just after their death ; a ghost , a spectre ” ) . [from 18th c.]
